This paper deals with the security and privacy of the Tor network, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The paper also proposes algorithms to estimate the number of snooping HSDirs and identify the most likely snoopers, which involves data analysis and algorithms, falling under the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of cloud infrastructure by misbehaving nodes, which falls under the category of cybercrime (cs.CY).
